ecouple\nfrom the low-energy effective Lagrangian, contributing only irrelevant\noperators after renormalization. The $\\nu_R^{M}$ cannot completely decouple,\nbut becomes invisible in practice. The NGB decouples, but our hidden SSB\n$U(1)_Y$ WTI, and a ${\\tilde \\pi}$ shift symmetry, protect the low-energy SSB\nAHM physics from loop contributions of heavy particles! Gauge-independent\nobservable weak-scale $m_{H;Pole}$ and $<H>$ are Goldstone Exceptionally\nNatural, not fine-tuned.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Sep 2015 05:44:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 14 Aug 2016 18:10:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-09"}
