termine the supernova type from the\nX-ray spectrum. Indirect evidence was found in the study of the local stellar\npopulation and star formation history in the literature, which suggests a\ncore-collapse origin. MCSNR J0512-6707 likely resulted from the core-collapse\nof high mass progenitor which carved a low density cavity into its surrounding\nmedium, with the soft X-rays resulting from the impact of the blast wave with\nthe surrounding shell. The unusual hard X-ray component requires deeper and\nhigher spatial resolution radio and X-ray observations to confirm its origin.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Sep 2015 06:41:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-04"}
